The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Sunday, June 20, 2004 				 Collision scare
																								Srinagar, June 19: A collision was narrowly averted at Srinagar airport yesterday by an alert Jet Airways pilot, reports our correspondent.																								The pilot, who had been cleared for take-off, noticed that a helicopter was preparing to land on the same strip. He immediately used his emergency brakes to halt the plane, on which former chief minister Farooq Abdullah and health minister Chowdhary Lal Singh were travelling.																								The pilot had been cleared for take-off by the ATC and the plane was speeding on the runway for take-off when he noticed a chopper approaching.... A certain disaster was averted due to the alertness of the pilot, an airway source said. 
